World Health Organization (WHO) data reveals that ONE in FOUR people are affected by mental health issues like anxiety and depression. This means you might have people around you - friends, classmates at school,
 family members - who might be going through some of these mental health issues.


Mental health, however, is a very stigmatized topic and does not easily make 
into our conversation in family, school or with friends. This video beautifully
 explains mental health and how to talk about mental health.